Package net.sf.jstuff.core.types

Class ExtensibleEnum<ID>

java.lang.Object
net.sf.jstuff.core.types.ExtensibleEnum<ID>
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
Direct Known Subclasses:
TypeSafeEnum
public abstract class ExtensibleEnum<ID> extends Object implements Serializable
An alternative to Enum that supports generics and inheritance. It is based on the type safe enum pattern described in Effective Java by Joshua Block.

It allows to compare enumeration objects by reference (==), rather than with .equals(), even if the enums were serialized and deserialized.

Author:
Sebastian Thomschke
